  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@andrewstephens If you want to make a menu select, you could [copy the menu connector](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/develop/src/connectors/menu/connectMenu.js) in your codebase and [follow the v2 guide](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/guides/customization.html) (that should work with v1). The only dependency of the connector is over `checkRendering` in the utils of instantsearch, you can discard the use of this test to remove this dependency.\r\n\r\nThis is not the nicest solution, but this is the best we can offer until the plugin moves forward and  uses InstantSearch.js v2.\r\n\r\nI am closing this issue. I suggest you add an issue in the plugin repo if you'd like the plug-in to support InstantSearch.js v2.",
    "created_at": "2018-01-25T14:28:24Z",
